Reports have flooded social media and national news, following the tragic death of the newly appointed leader of the LUMISA union, Sifiso Maphumalo.Sifiso Maphumalo and three others were involved in a motor vehicle crash along the N3, South Bound about 12 kilometers from Ultra City, late last night. KZNems responded to the scene of the crash and the Jaws of Life had to be utilized to free the entrapped. It has been reported that the three other people had sustained slight injuries.It has been reported that the LUMISA leader was on his way to an inauguration by COSATU in Johannesburg today. Colenso police have opened a case of culpable homicide to investigate the cause of the crash. More information to follow&nbsp;